Document: ImageFormatLoaderExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_imageformatloaderextension.rst
Summary: Methods for handling image format recognition and loading in the engine.

Method: _get_recognized_extensions() → PackedStringArray
Returns the list of file extensions for this image format. Files with the given extensions will be treated as image files and loaded using this class. Note: This method must be implemented by subclasses to define supported extensions.

Method: _load_image(image: Image, fileaccess: FileAccess, flags: LoaderFlags, scale: float) → Error
Loads the content of fileaccess into the provided image. Parameters:
- image (Image): Target image to populate with loaded data
- fileaccess (FileAccess): File access object containing the image data
- flags (LoaderFlags): Bitfield of loading options (e.g., LOAD_FLAG_MIPMAPS)
- scale (float): Scaling factor for the image dimensions
Returns: Error indicating success or failure of the operation.

Method: add_format_loader() → void
Registers this format loader with the engine, enabling it to recognize file extensions returned by _get_recognized_extensions(). Must be called after implementation to activate the loader.

Method: remove_format_loader() → void
Unregisters this format loader from the engine, preventing it from handling any image files. Typically used when disabling or removing a custom image format handler.